description:
Japanese title: Kessei! Saiaku no Taggu, 結成！最悪のタッグ.

On their flight into the Seireitei, Ichigo and the others are separated.
name: Formation! The Worst Tag

description:
Japanese title: Hissatsu no Ichigeki o Hanate! 必殺の一撃を放て！.

Within the Seireitei, a full-fledged search for the intruders--the "ryoka"--is put into action. Rukia is transferred to the Repentance Cell to await her execution...
name: Release The Death Blow!

description:
Japanese title: Nerawareta Orihime 狙われた織姫.

Forced to stay alert and on their toes, Ichigo and his fellow ryoka continue to be hunted by Soul Reapers.
name: Orihime Targeted

description:
Japanese title: Toppa seyo! Shinigami Hōimō 突破せよ！死神包囲網.

News of the intruders' surprising strength spreads among the Soul Reapers, and the captains are eager for information.
name: Breakthrough! The Shinigami's Encompassing Net

description:
Japanese title: Tachihadakaru Renji 立ちはだかる恋次.

Hanataro leads Ichigo and Ganju toward the Repentance Cell where Rukia is being held...
name: Renji's Confrontation

description:
Japanese title: Kiru Tame no Kakugo 斬る為の覚悟.

Renji and Ichigo engage in battle...
name: The Resolution To Kill

description:
Japanese title: Hoshi to Norainu 星と野良犬.

Renji faces defeat, and in his last moments recalls his childhood with Rukia in the Rukongai district of the Soul Society.
name: Stars And The Stray

description:
Japanese title: Kiseki! Nazo no Shin Hīrō 奇跡！謎の新ヒーロー.

In the world of the living, Ichigo's sisters Karin and Yuzu are recruited by television personality Don Kanonji to learn how to fight bad spirits...
name: Miracle! The Mysterious New Hero

description: In the milestone 26th season opener of The Simpsons, the unthinkable happens: a Springfield resident dies. Also, Krusty retires after he's offended by a comedy cable channel roast of him, and Lisa tries to protect Homer from getting hurt.
name: Clown in the Dumps

description: When Bart disrespects Homer's authority, Homer makes a point to try his hand at parenting. This proves fruitless, so Marge signs them up for the Relation Ship, where they'll resolve their conflicts at sea. Meanwhile, Marge is in charge of Homer's fantasy football league, but manages to win despite being the underdog.
name: The Wreck of the Relationship

description: Marge opens a sandwich franchise store after her sandwiches become a huge hit at Springfield Elementary. But running day-to-day at the store proves challenging, especially when the same franchise opens another location across the street.
name: Super Franchise Me

description: On the annual spooktacular Halloween special, Bart and Lisa are transported to a demon-filled alternate universe after Bart reads a set of Aramaic symbols he finds on the underside of his desk; Moe's Clockwork Orange-style gang is disrupted when Dum (Homer) falls for a girl (Marge) who wants him to give up the thug life; and, in an homage to The Others, the Simpsons are visited by their former Tracey Ullman-era versions of themselves.
name: Treehouse of Horror XXV

description: Lisa brings in Assemblywoman Maxine Lombard to put a stop to Mr. Burns' fracking operation, but is taken aback when the two political opponents find themselves attracted to one another.
name: Opposites A-Frack

description: Bart faces a tough test at school when he gets a new teacher, Mr. Lassen (guest voice Willem Dafoe), who vows to crush his spirit.
name: Blazed and Confused

description: Homer has a mid-life crisis after Moe's shuts down and Moe (Hank Azaria) takes off on a trip with King Toot (guest voice Will Forte). When Homer takes up the bass guitar and forms a cover band with some of the other dads in town, their modest early success is soon overwhelmed by the breakout potential of their most unlikely star: Apu (Azaria).
name: Covercraft

description: After Moe convinces Homer to stay out drinking on Christmas Eve, Marge tells Homer not to come home. This leads to Homer's sad trek through lonely Springfield, where he learns that the only place where one should truly get drunk on Christmas is home.
name: I Won't Be Home for Christmas

description: During a trip to Dizzneeland, the Simpsons board the wrong ride, Rocket To Your Doom, and are transported through the galaxy to Kang and Kodos' home planet, where they are held captive at the local zoo and the inhabitants decide to eat Homer.
name: The Man Who Came to Be Dinner

description: Bart has a new accomplice and best friend when Homer is hypnotized at the circus and believes he is a young boy again.
name: Bart's New Friend

description: Peter helps Joe publish a book, but then takes over as author.
name: The Book of Joe

description: Lois and Peter go into business together and open a cookie store, but things get messy when Peter comes up with his own way to get more customers.
name: Baking Bad

description: Brian's cosmetic surgery leads him down a new career path as a real estate agent, which gets him into trouble with Quagmire.
name: Brian the Closer

description: On the night before Thanksgiving, Brian and Peter drunkenly devour the holiday bird, and then must go out to find a replacement. In Peter's absence, Chris attempts to step up and become the man of the house.
name: Turkey Guys

description: Happy Birthday, Jesus.
name: The 2000-Year-Old Virgin

description: To help Chris ace his ninth grade history class, Stewie and Brian employ the time travel machine for educational purposes. Not surprisingly, all three get stuck in the past.
name: Stewie, Chris & Brian's Excellent Adventure

description: Meg convinces Brian to take the SAT's for her, but when he tests poorly, they start to suspect that Brian might not that smart after all. Peter decides to spend the day showing Brian the joys of being stupid and the benefits of having a low IQ.
name: Our Idiot Brian

description: Det. Gordon's assignment at Arkham Asylum gets off to a rocky start when the murder of a guard ignites an investigation, leading him to meet Dr. Leslie Thompkins (guest-star Morena Baccarin). Meanwhile, Cobblepot continues to build his army.
name: Rogues' Gallery

description: In an attempt to get his job back, Gordon seeks to capture Jack Gruber (guest-star Christopher Heyerdahl), a deranged electrical genius who escapes Arkham Asylum. Meanwhile, Falcone struggles to hold onto his empire after Fish Mooney makes her next move.
name: What the Little Bird Told Him

description:
Japanese title: Yoake no Sangeki, 夜明けの惨劇.

Word of Renji's defeat spreads, and all-out war is declared against the ryoka...
name: Tradegy Of Dawn
The Warner's Lot Song/The Big Candy Store/Bumbie's Mom

description:
Japanese title: Aizen Ansatsu! Shinobiyoru Yami, 藍染暗殺！忍び寄る闇.

A prominent captain of the Soul Reapers is found dead, and Soul Reapers turn against one another in a flurry of suspicion and accusation.
name: Aizen Assassinated! The Darkness Which Approaches

description:
Japanese title: Zaraki Kenpachi, Semaru!, 更木剣八、迫る！.

Ichigo, Ganju and Hanataro climb the great staircase of the Senzaikyu--the White Tower--only to sense an unprecedented amount of spirit energy.
name: Kenpachi Zaraki Approaches!

description:
Japanese title: Kobushi no Riyū, 拳の理由.

Chad's journey to the Senzaikyu is interrupted by the captain of Squad 8…
name: Motive Of The Fist

description:
Japanese title: Zettaizetsumei! Orareta Zangetsu, 絶対絶命！折られた斬月.

Ichigo, still battling Captain Zaraki, senses a loss of Chad's spirit energy and fears the worst…
name: Desperation! The Broken Zangetsu

description:
Japanese title: Fujimi no Otoko, 不死身の男.

Lying weak with sword wounds on the ground, Ichigo is greeted by a vision of an embodied version of his zanpaku-to…
name: The Immortal Man

description:
Japanese title: Ganju no Mita Shinigami, 岩鷲の見た死神.

Ganju and Hanataro continue toward the Senzaikyu to save Rukia…
name: The Shinigami Whom Ganju Met

description:
Japanese title: Saikai, Ichigo to Rukia 再会,、一護とルキア.

Sensing great spirit energy near the Repentance Cell, Ichigo defies Yoruichi's orders and flees to assist Ganju and Hanataro.
name: Reunion, Ichigo and Rukia

description:
Japanese title: Shunjin Yoruichi, Mau! 瞬神夜一、舞う！.

Orihime decides that the quickest way to get to Rukia is for she and Uryu to disguise themselves as Soul Reapers.
name: Yoruichi, Goddess Of Flash, Dances!

description:
Japanese title: Hiretsu na Shinigami, 卑劣な死神.

Orihime and Uryu, dressed as Soul Reapers, are offered help by Squad 12, but Uryu quickly realizes that the jig is up and the offer is a trap.
name: The Despicable Shinigami

description:
Japanese title: Ishida, Kyokugen no Chikara! 石田、極限の力！

The captain decides that rather than kill Uryu, he wishes to capture him and study his distinctive abilities.
name: Ishida's Ultimate Power!

description:
Japanese title: Genkai o Koero! 限界を越えろ！

Yoruichi trains Ichigo in the finer points of using his zanpaku-to...
name: Overcome Your Limits!

description:
Japanese title: Jitsuroku! Shinigami no Gakkō, 実録！死神の学校.

Momo recalls her days at the Soul Reaper Academy, where she met and trained in the World of the Living...
name: Authentic Records! School Of Shinigami

description:
Japanese title: Adautsu Mono-tachi, 仇討つ者たち.

Momo, Renji and Kira have all escaped.
name: The Avengers

description:
Japanese title: Hitsugaya, Hoeru!JI'J' 日番谷、吼える！

In her holding cell, Rukia has a dream that she believes is to help her prepare for the next day's events.
name: Hitsugaya Roars!

description:
Japanese title: Rukia no Akumu ルキアの悪夢.

In her dream, Rukia recalls her time spent training under Lieutenant Kaien and Captain Ukitate.
name: Rukia's NIghtmare
